  "notes": [
    {
      "id": "note_1",
      "text": "SINE WAVES ARE EVERYWHERE — NZ Yr 12–13\n\nHidden truth: midline (mesor) 50, amplitude 40, period 24 h, acrophase (peak) at 8:00, plus noise (sd 5). The Cosinor fit should recover these; R² near 1 means the cosine model fits well.\n\nCurriculum (NZ): NZC M8-7 / M7-2 (trig modelling & graphs); NCEA AS91575 (trig methods). Intl: AP Precalc trig, A-level Trig, IB composite trig a·sin(b(x+c))+d.\nNCEA is transitional: L1 removed from 2028; NZCE (Yr12) 2029; NZACE (Yr13) 2030. Standards below remain valid through the change.\n\nFull mapping + worked walkthrough: classroom-handbook.html",
      "x": 40,
      "y": 40,
      "width": 380,
      "height": 240
    }
